      "authors": "Kalmykov, Mikhail Yu., Kniehl, Bernd A.",
      "description": "Two-loop self-energy sunset-type diagram J_{012}(sigma,beta,alpha) with three internal propagators (one massless, two massive with masses M and m) and on-shell external kinematics p^2 = -m^2 (Euclidean signature in the paper). Defined in Eq. (J012) and shown in Fig. 1. Standard IBP reduction (Tarasov, Laporta) yields three nontrivial master integrals J_{012}(1,1,1), J_{012}(1,2,1), J_{012}(1,1,2), but the differential-reduction criteria of Refs. [Kalmykov, BKK, review] give only two. The paper derives a new algebraic relation, Eq. (main): (3n-8)J_{012}(1,1,1) + 4 m^2 J_{012}(1,2,1) + 2 M^2 J_{012}(1,1,2) = 2 (M^2)^{n-3} Gamma(n/2-1) Gamma(3-n) Gamma(2-n/2), which contains a Gamma-function inhomogeneity and therefore cannot be obtained from standard IBP. The hypergeometric representation, Eq. (J012:hyper), expresses J_{012} in terms of two _4F_3 functions (reducing to _2F_1 and _3F_2) of argument z = 4 m^2/M^2. For the equal-mass case m^2 = M^2 the auxiliary relation Eq. (aux) reproduces Eq. (4.45) of Ref. [DK01]. Diagram contributes to the top-quark pole-mass calculation.",
